    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- Nvim: v.0.4.4\r\n- Operating system/version: Arch Linux 5.10.35-1-lts\r\n- Terminal name/version: Konsole, 21.04.1\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nIf this report is about different behaviour between Nvim and Vim, make sure to\r\nread `:h vim-differences` first. Otherwise remove the next line.\r\n-->\r\n[X] `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: 8.2) behaves the same.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\n- nvim -u NORC\r\n- Place cursor on arabic text. \r\n- Move cursor around\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nBasically this (wait for it, it is a slow gif):\r\n![issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57800665/120313636-f09ab400-c2e2-11eb-9dba-303cc6e267c7.gif)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThere should be an option that allows users to turn this off.\r\n\r\nWhy is this the default behavior? (This seems to be a recent change)\r\n\r\nThis feature/bug is very confusing and does not help me at all in editing arabic texts personally. \r\n",
